    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 3, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For protection of American schools, this Government, while recognizing right of
                    Turkey to punish her own subjects for violating her own laws, will insist that
                    native teachers shall not be arrested arbitrarily or capriciously. Not necessary
                    to take position that arrests can not be made without your consent. Instructions
                    by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
